cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about salient object detection using fully convolutional neural networks (FCNs) and edge information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which involves modeling complementary information, and this falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training the network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
